   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Account of expenses:;for the service to the thieves &lt;read probably: thief-catchers&gt;: 10 &lt;drachmai&gt;;for a papyrus roll to cut: 2 drachmai;for fodder, for 3 camels: 7 &lt;drachmai&gt; 16 obols;for ink: 2 &lt;drachmai&gt; 6 obols;to the assistant: 2 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the beneficiarius: 15 &lt;drachmai&gt;;for garlands and pine-cones: 4 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the carpenter: 20 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the door-keeper: 2 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to Harpokration the carrier: 12 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to Hermenios: 12 &lt;drachmai&gt;;&lt;to those&gt; in the fields(?): 15 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the assistant: 2 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the (messenger) going to the epistrategos: 15 &lt;drachmai&gt;;for a bench: 2 drachmai;&lt;to the messenger going&gt; to the court of the prefect: [*]20 drachmai;to Harpalos: 9 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the assistants who are with Heras: 3 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the president: 25 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to those (who manage) the unsold properties: 7[*] &lt;drachmai&gt;;to Anoubion: 50 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the clerk: 40 &lt;drachmai&gt;;to the lawyers: 40 &lt;drachmai&gt;;for the slaves: 35 &lt;drachmai&gt;;for the slaves of the royal &lt;scribe&gt;: 2 &lt;drachmai&gt;</ab>
         </div>
